Course : End-to-End Enterprise application
PreRequisite : Good Java Knowledge and Hands-on
Topics: Spring, Maven, Hibernate, Spring boot, Mongo, Linux basic commands, kafka, junit,
Rest application


0) Depedency Injection & Inversion of control
1) sample spring project - beans.xml
2) sample spring project - annotations(@Configuration , @Bean)
3) sample spring project - annotations(@Configuration, @Component)
4) Maven phases(validate,compile,package,install,deploy) and goals(clean)
5) Maven parent child project
6) Maven creating own plugin
7) Profiles and Scopes
8) PropertySource(@Value, Enviornment, spel(spring evaluation expression language))
9) Qualifiers
10) Linux basic commands
11) Introduction to SQL
12) Hibernate setup and sample project
13) Hibernate integrated with Spring
14) Spring boot creating using spring initialzr
15) Spring boot sample rest project
16) Spring boot - Spring data jpa integrate hibernate project in Chapter 13(end-end project)
17) Spring boot - Cloud configuration
18) Spring boot - Configuration Properties
19) Spring boot - hystrix netfix- circuit breaker
20) Introduction to MongoDB
21) Spring boot - rest controller - mongodb
22) Spring boot - exception handling techniques , implementation in Chapter 16 and Chapter 21
23) Introduction to Kafka and setup
24) Spring boot - implementing kafka in spring boot
23) Spring Junit test cases
23) Jenkins file - build jobs
24) Introduction to PCF
25) Deployment to PCF

Duration : 40+ hours
